ACME AGENT SUPPLY CO.

PRIVACY POLICY
Effective Date: [________] | Last Updated: March 2, 2026

Acme Agent Supply Co. ("Acme," "we," "us," or "our") is committed to minimizing data collection and keeping operators in control.

This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our website and software tools (the "Tools").

⸻

1. Our Approach

ACME Tools are designed to operate locally and in read-only mode by default.

We aim to:

• collect as little data as possible
• avoid unnecessary telemetry
• keep operators in control of their environments
• be explicit when data leaves your machine

Most functionality works without sending data to Acme.

⸻

2. Information We May Receive

Information you provide

We may receive information you choose to provide, such as:

• email address (for updates or support)
• support requests or messages
• Proof Bundles or diagnostic files you voluntarily share
• billing information for paid services

You control whether this information is shared.

⸻

Limited website data

When you visit acmeagentsupply.com, we may automatically receive basic technical data such as:

• IP address
• browser and device type
• referring pages
• basic usage analytics

This information is used only to operate and secure the site and understand aggregate usage.

We do not inspect your local environments.

⸻

Tool behavior (important)

ACME Tools:

• run primarily in your local environment
• do not transmit operational data to Acme by default
• do not access your systems remotely
• do not exfiltrate Proof Bundles unless you choose to share them

⸻

3. Optional Telemetry

Some Paid Tier features may offer optional telemetry.

Where telemetry exists:

• it is clearly disclosed
• it is disabled by default
• it activates only with your consent
• you may disable it at any time

We do not enable hidden telemetry.

⸻

4. How We Use Information

If we receive information from you, we use it to:

• provide and support the Tools
• respond to support requests
• process payments (if applicable)
• maintain security

We do not sell or rent your personal information. We may share limited information with service providers that help us operate the Site (for example, hosting, analytics, or email delivery), only as needed to provide the service.


⸻

5. Data Retention

We retain personal information only as long as reasonably necessary to:

• provide requested services
• comply with legal obligations
• resolve disputes
• enforce agreements

⸻

6. Security

We implement reasonable safeguards appropriate to the information we handle. However, no system can be guaranteed completely secure.

Operators remain responsible for the security of their own environments.

⸻

7. Changes

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be reflected by the "Last Updated" date.

